<p>October 1915</p>
<p>Wednesday 6</p>
<p>goes round the hill parallel with the trenches then leaving the road turns to the left towards the sea, &amp; sharply down. Thence it is downhill all the way to a road which leads to the sap before mentioned.</p>
<p>Total distance about 1 mile.</p>
<p>A bearer has to keep going on either of these tracks under heavy shrapnel fire for 24 hours or more when a charge is on, dark or light.</p>
<p>Thus he does his bit.</p>
